                  <h1 class="title node-type-og">SecondLife</h1>
                              <div id="node-1634" class="node clear-block">



  <div class="meta">
  
    </div>

  <div class="content">
    <div id="mission"><div class="box"><div class="w1"><div class="w2"><div class="w3"><div class="w4"><p>Hey I'd like to form a group of SLers that are interested in conceiving and developing Drupal modules to support effective integration of Drupal online communities w/ SL online communities-- and then showing others how to do it well.</p>
<p>Tons of questions to look into-- how would you share content two ways between an SL "group" and a "group" in the "organic groups" paradigm of Drupal?   How can you most easily post your Drupal based videoblog to your SL home?  How can you grab conversations and visitor metrics from SL (which can still support ~80 people simultaneously in one place is that still correct?) and report them to your larger community on your Drupal site that can support 10,000s of concurrent users, etc. etc.?</p>
<p>Some of the Drupal sites related to SecondLife that we know of include:</p>
<p><a href="http://www.lindenlab.com" title="http://www.lindenlab.com">http://www.lindenlab.com</a><br />
<a href="http://teen.secondlife.com" title="http://teen.secondlife.com">http://teen.secondlife.com</a><br />
<a href="http://www.infoisland.org/drupal/" title="http://www.infoisland.org/drupal/">http://www.infoisland.org/drupal/</a><br />
<a href="http://zorin.org/drupal/" title="http://zorin.org/drupal/">http://zorin.org/drupal/</a><br />
<a href="http://slispaceflightmuseum.org/drupal/" title="http://slispaceflightmuseum.org/drupal/">http://slispaceflightmuseum.org/drupal/</a><br />
<a href="http://www.webheadsinaction.org/" title="http://www.webheadsinaction.org/">http://www.webheadsinaction.org/</a></p>
<p>Please submit your ideas for useful module functionality for effective Drupal/SL integration.</p>
</div></div></div></div></div></div><div class="view view-og-ghp-ron view-id-og_ghp_ron view-display-id-default view-dom-id-1">
    
  
  
