  <h2><a href="/node/2949" title="SecondLife Drupal Framework released">SecondLife Drupal Framework released</a></h2>

  <div class="meta">
      <span class="submitted">Submitted by <a href="/user/327" title="View user profile.">kbahey</a> on Mon, 2007-02-26 16:31</span>
  
      <div class="terms terms-inline"><a href="/taxonomy/term/1607" rel="tag" title="">2bits</a> · <a href="/taxonomy/term/1606" rel="tag" title="">Drupal SecondLife</a> · <a href="/taxonomy/term/1605" rel="tag" title="">linden labs</a> · <a href="/taxonomy/term/1604" rel="tag" title="">secondlife</a></div>
    </div>

  <div class="content">
    <div class="vote-up-down-widget">
      <span id="vote_up_2949" class="up-inact" title="You must login to vote!"></span>
    <span id="vote_down_2949" class="down-inact" title="You must login to vote!"></span>
  </div>
<p><a href="http://2bits.com">2bits</a> has released a <a href="http://drupal.org/project/secondlife">Drupal SecondLife framework</a>.</p>
<p>This allows modules to interact with SecondLife objects, and handle requests from in world.</p>
<p>A sample application and a test client is included.</p>
  </div>
  
  
