  <h2><a href="/node/1754" title="Good Analog to look to: Moodle+SecondLife">Good Analog to look to: Moodle+SecondLife</a></h2>

  <div class="meta">
      <span class="submitted">Submitted by <a href="/user/110" title="View user profile.">ahoppin</a> on Fri, 2006-11-03 00:05</span>
  
      <div class="terms terms-inline"><a href="/taxonomy/term/984" rel="tag" title="">Moodle SecondLife Linden</a></div>
    </div>

  <div class="content">
    <div class="vote-up-down-widget">
      <span id="vote_up_1754" class="up-inact" title="You must login to vote!"></span>
    <span id="vote_down_1754" class="down-inact" title="You must login to vote!"></span>
  </div>
<p><a href="http://www.sloodle.com" title="http://www.sloodle.com">http://www.sloodle.com</a></p>
<p>Thanks to Troy McLuhan (<a href="http://groups.drupal.org/user/2566" title="http://groups.drupal.org/user/2566">http://groups.drupal.org/user/2566</a>) for pointing this out to me.  Looks like a great analog for us to look to, especially in light of efforts already underway to integrate Moodle and Drupal.</p>
